Durban - The State on Wednesday withdrew assault charges against five Durban schoolgirls after they completed a National Institute for Crime Prevention and the Reintegration of Offenders (Nicro) diversion programme.A video recording of a bullying incident at Bechet Secondary School in June was posted on social media showing a group of schoolgirls, aged between 16 and 18, beating a school pupil who allegedly kissed the boyfriend of one of the girls. The incident took place in the girls&#x2019; toilet.They were charged with assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm and were released into their parents&#x2019; custody.The matter was referred to Nicro for mediation. The non-profit organisation specialises in social crime prevention and offender re-integration.On Wednesday, the Durban Magistrate&#x2019;s Court heard that the girls had completed a Youth Empowerment Scheme from August 11 to September 29.Based on this, the Nicro social worker recommended that charges be withdrawn.